<task id="021" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Tool Registry — CRUD &amp; Query Endpoints</title>
    <phase>Phase 2: Tool Registry + Discovery</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <blocks>030, 040</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, api, endpoints, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF endpoint code with endpoint-filter auth (ADR-008), ProblemDetails (ADR-019), audit middleware (ADR-015); blocks Phase 3+ discovery UI work; tags include bff-api + ai + endpoints</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Distinct scope (endpoints) from Group C meta-tools (022/023/024 — service implementations) and from tasks 025/026 (registration + dispatch). Endpoints depend only on task 020's data model. Touches `Api/Ai/ToolRegistryEndpoints.cs` + `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` registration — no file overlap with siblings.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement `ToolRegistryEndpoints.cs` — the BFF Minimal API endpoint surface for Tool Registry CRUD + query operations. Endpoints serve the Tool Registry admin UI (Phase 5 surfaces) and the Action authoring UI. Apply ADR-008 endpoint-filter authorization, ADR-019 ProblemDetails error responses, and wire the endpoints into `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` via a `MapToolRegistryEndpoints()` extension.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET 8 Minimal API engineer with strong familiarity with the Spaarke BFF endpoint conventions (`Api/` folder + `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` registration site), endpoint-filter authorization (ADR-008), and ProblemDetails error responses (ADR-019).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three concrete outcomes:
    1. **CRUD endpoints** — GET (list, by-id), POST (create), PUT (update), DELETE — backed by the `sprk_toolregistry` Dataverse entity (read/write via existing Dataverse client). All endpoints apply endpoint-filter auth per ADR-008.
    2. **Query endpoints** — `GET /api/tool-registry?classification=&amp;costClass=&amp;isAlwaysOn=` filtered queries used by the admin UI and by the `FindResources` semantic-search filter step (e.g., authorization filter).
    3. **Registration** — `MapToolRegistryEndpoints()` extension added to `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs`; route group prefix `/api/tool-registry`. ProblemDetails error responses for 400/404/409/500.

    Deliverable: `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ToolRegistryEndpoints.cs` + extension method in `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs`; integration test stub at `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Api/Ai/ToolRegistryEndpointsTests.cs`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 020 produced the `ToolRegistryEntry` data model. This task wires that model into BFF endpoint surface. Consumers:
      - Tool Registry admin UI (Phase 5 SpaarkeAi extensions) for human-managed Tool registration
      - `FindResourcesTool` (task 022) calls neither this endpoint nor the Dataverse entity directly — it queries AI Search. But the admin UI does write via these endpoints, which trigger the AI Search indexer (out-of-band, task 016 already wired).
      - Action authoring UI for Tool selection

      Existing BFF endpoint patterns to mirror:
      - `Endpoints/EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` line ~157 — `MapActionEndpoints()` slot adjacent
      - `Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs` — pattern for AI-prefixed endpoint groups
      - Endpoint-filter auth pattern: `.AddEndpointFilter&lt;RequireSdapPermissionFilter&gt;("ToolRegistry.Manage")` or similar

      `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` is shared with other Phase 2 / Phase 4 tasks; ONLY this task adds the `MapToolRegistryEndpoints()` call site. Tasks 025 / 040 add their own slots at distinct line ranges — no merge conflict expected if each task touches its own line range.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ToolRegistryEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Endpoints/EndpointMappingExtensions.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ToolRegistry/ToolRegistryModel.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Filters/RequireSdapPermissionFilter.cs</file>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Api/Ai/ToolRegistryEndpointsTests.cs</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/design.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API. Endpoint groups via `app.MapGroup("/api/tool-registry")`. No controllers.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint-filter authorization REQUIRED on every endpoint via `.AddEndpointFilter&lt;&gt;()`. NO global middleware. Read endpoints: `ToolRegistry.Read`; Write endpoints: `ToolRegistry.Manage`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism. Endpoint dependencies (Dataverse client, JsonSerializerOptions from task 020) resolved via `[FromServices]`. No service-locator anti-patterns.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">PublicContracts boundary. This endpoint is BFF-internal — does NOT need facade exposure. But the response shape (ToolRegistryEntry) lives in AE-internal namespace; that's OK because the endpoint is the seam.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Audit middleware applies automatically; no manual audit calls. Tier 2 hash will fingerprint the request/response body.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">All error responses use ProblemDetails (RFC 7807). 400 = validation; 404 = not found; 409 = duplicate ToolId; 500 = unexpected. Include `traceId`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">No new NuGet packages. Use existing Dataverse client (`IDataverseClient` or equivalent) for reads/writes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge: placement justification (in BFF — endpoint serves AE-managed admin UI; latency-sensitive write path triggers index refresh). No CRUD→AI direct deps.</constraint>
  </constraints>

