    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Minimal API endpoint definition" location=".claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md">`MapGroup` + endpoint method extraction; `[FromServices]` for DI; explicit return types.</pattern>
      <pattern name="Endpoint filter auth" location=".claude/patterns/api/endpoint-filters.md">`.AddEndpointFilter&lt;RequireSdapPermissionFilter&gt;(permission)` per endpoint; ADR-008 binding.</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm baseline build passes; task 020 merged or its branch loadable; baseline `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` line numbers known.</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;`. Pay attention to ADR-008 (endpoint filter), ADR-019 (ProblemDetails), `.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md`, and bff-extensions.md.</step>
    <step order="2">Sketch endpoint surface: `GET /api/tool-registry` (list with filter query params), `GET /api/tool-registry/{toolId}` (by-id), `POST /api/tool-registry` (create), `PUT /api/tool-registry/{toolId}` (update), `DELETE /api/tool-registry/{toolId}` (soft-delete via `IsActive=false`). Document expected status codes + ProblemDetails error shapes.</step>
    <step order="3">Implement `ToolRegistryEndpoints.cs`: static class with `MapToolRegistryEndpoints(this IEndpointRouteBuilder app)` extension. Each endpoint method is a static handler. Use the model from task 020. Apply `.AddEndpointFilter&lt;RequireSdapPermissionFilter&gt;("ToolRegistry.Read")` to read endpoints and `("ToolRegistry.Manage")` to writes.</step>
    <step order="4">Implement query endpoint filtering by `classification`, `costClass`, `isAlwaysOnInAssistant`, `discoverabilitySearchable`, plus a `phase` filter that returns Tools eligible for a given phase (NOT in deny list). Wire to Dataverse client.</step>
    <step order="5">Wire ProblemDetails for all error paths. 400 = validation (e.g., missing required fields on create); 404 = ToolId not found; 409 = duplicate ToolId on create; 500 = unexpected — include `traceId` from Activity.Current.</step>
    <step order="6">Add `MapToolRegistryEndpoints()` call into `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs`. Locate the existing `MapActionEndpoints()` slot (task 040 will add that; for now place adjacent under `// AI Action Engine endpoints` comment). Verify the route prefix doesn't collide with existing groups.</step>
    <step order="7">Write integration test stub at `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Api/Ai/ToolRegistryEndpointsTests.cs`: smoke tests for each verb. Use `WebApplicationFactory&lt;Program&gt;`. Verify (a) 401 without auth, (b) 403 without permission, (c) 200/201/204 with permission, (d) ProblemDetails shape on 404.</step>
    <step order="8">Verify build + tests: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` + `dotnet test tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~ToolRegistry"`.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify NFR-10: no new NuGet packages. `git diff src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj` shows zero package changes.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` on new files; `adr-check` verifies ADR-008 (endpoint filters on EVERY endpoint), ADR-010 (no service-locator anti-patterns), ADR-019 (ProblemDetails everywhere), ADR-029 (no new packages).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 021 ✅. Update `current-task.md` accordingly.</step>
    <step order="11">Document any deviations in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/`. Commit with brief recap.</step>
  </steps>

