  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All five CRUD verbs implemented (GET list, GET by-id, POST, PUT, DELETE) on route prefix `/api/tool-registry`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every endpoint has `.AddEndpointFilter&lt;RequireSdapPermissionFilter&gt;(...)` applied — verified by grep + ADR-008 adr-check.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Query endpoint supports filtering by `classification`, `costClass`, `isAlwaysOnInAssistant`, `phase` query params — verified by integration test.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All error responses use ProblemDetails shape (RFC 7807) with `traceId` — verified by ADR-019 adr-check + integration test 404 case.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`MapToolRegistryEndpoints()` registered in `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs`; route prefix doesn't collide with existing groups.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Integration tests pass: 401 unauthenticated, 403 forbidden, 200/201/204 happy path, 404 ProblemDetails — `dotnet test --filter "ToolRegistry"` exits 0.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new NuGet packages added (NFR-10 preserved).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Supports spec gate G11 (every Action Engine endpoint has endpoint-filter auth) — verified by adr-check Step 9.5.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` is a shared file touched by Phase 2 task 025 (always-on Tools wire-up) and Phase 4 task 040 (`MapActionEndpoints`). Each task adds its own call line at a distinct location. Use a comment marker (`// Action Engine endpoints — task 021/025/040`) to make per-task additions clearly attributable.

    Audit middleware (ADR-015) hashes request/response automatically — no manual audit calls needed in this task.

    DELETE is soft-delete (`IsActive=false`) not hard-delete, because Tool Registry rows are referenced by historical `sprk_actionrun` records and audit trail.
  </notes>

